cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep learning model for multimodal learning. The model is trained using backpropagation and Contrastive Divergence, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed model is applied to visual restoration, labeling, and object recognition tasks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the model is capable of learning shared representations for multiple inputs and outputs, which is a common problem in AI. 

Furthermore, it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) as the proposed model is designed to handle multiple modalities, such as visual and textual inputs. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed model is a deep neural network and uses backpropagation to update the model parameters.
